1.title: Ambushed
1.plot: A boss of a group of corporate raiders suffers a heart attack on a cliff on a bonding exercise Rescue is gazumped by Lifeblood - the new private enterprise rescue outfit - and their team leader Cam.

2.title: Fearless
2.plot: Dean tries to help a man who has become trapped in his car following an accident, but the victim makes surprising decisions after being told he is unlikely to survive.

3.title: True Romance
3.plot: The team are dispatched to a foggy ravine where a couple, Michael and Katie Pitt, have gone over. Katie dies and initially Lara feels for Michael but begins to suspect something isn't right when he repeatedly looks for the return of a duffel bag. Lara finds it and also sees a drug packet and mentions it to Katie's sister who takes matters into her own hands when she realises that Michael had turned her sister psychotic with a mixture of drugs. Elsewhere, Jordan and Chase are drawn into the middle of a paint-ball fire-fight between the owners of the company. Meanwhile,...

4.title: Secrets and Lies
4.plot: Heidi rescues a girl who was found alone on a cliff, discovering she has mysterious injuries and her friends are trapped in a cave.

5.title: Him or Me
5.plot: Chase treats a man who allegedly tried to commit suicide, and Lara struggles to cope with the breakdown of her marriage.

6.title: Demon Days
6.plot: Dancers at a Gay Pride festival rehearsal become trapped under a float, while Jordan and Heidi discover Freya's flat has been ransacked.

7.title: Man in the Machine
7.plot: Because of Chase's shoulder injury, he switches work assignments with Vince, which gets challenging for both: When a man get his arm stuck in a machine, mysterious things happens and Lara goes missing.

8.title: The Game
8.plot: The team is called out to rescue a refuse collector who is trapped in his truck, and discover a seemingly suicidal woman standing on the roof of an office building.

9.title: It's Not the Fall That Kills You
9.plot: A rescue on a tall building goes wrong and suddenly Lara is the only one keeping both Dean and Cam from falling to the ground.

10.title: Stolen
10.plot: Michelle discovers an intruder photocopying confidential documents in her office, but the ensuing chase leads to the criminal being hit by a car.

11.title: In Deep
11.plot: The team recovers an injured fisherman, only to learn that another person is stranded on a cliff. Michelle also accepts a job with Lifeblood.

12.title: Break Out
12.plot: A prison bus containing female inmates overturns on a motorway and the team treats the injured passengers, but one of the felon's steals a guards gun.

13.title: The Dunes
13.plot: Members of the team test out their new quad bikes on the Kurnell dunes, only to stumble across a seriously injured boy in a smashed-up buggy.

14.title: Chemical Brothers
14.plot: A light plane that could not be contacted crashes into a customs yard, leading the team to launch a full-scale rescue operation.

15.title: The Carter Redemption
15.plot: Heidi and Jordan look forward to time alone after a rescue, only for a gang of bikers to demand their help because two of their friends have crashed into a cafe.

16.title: Storm Chaser
16.plot: Heidi and Jordan try to rescue a storm chaser trapped in an up-turned car, but the wind threatens to push the vehicle over a cliff.

17.title: Art Attack
17.plot: A cleaner impales himself on a valuable steel sculpture at an art gallery, and Dean tries to bond with Zoe's son Noah.

18.title: Missing Pieces
18.plot: Helen Hillerstrom asks the team for help when her son disappears in the Blue Mountains, 10 years after her husband vanished without a trace.

19.title: Class of Their Own
19.plot: A balcony collapses at a party, trapping some of the revellers, but the rescue is hindered by drunken teenagers.

20.title: The Intervention
20.plot: Lara and Dean discover a missing prospector has abducted his children and taken them into the Bush.

21.title: Bad Company
21.plot: The Gallagher brothers are forced to improvise to help an injured kitesurfer, who asks Jordan on a date when she recovers.

22.title: Two Fires
22.plot: In the last ever episode the team is stretched to its limit when a truck crashes into a service station, and Lara and Lachie treat a mechanic who has been crushed under a car.

1.title: Rescue in the Blue Mountains
1.plot: The team are dispatched to the Blue Mountains National Park to find two high school students, Joel and Cassie, who have gone missing from their camp overnight. Whilst there Dean and Lara discover the body of a missing pilot - hundreds of kilometers from his flight path - but no sign of his fellow passenger and girlfriend Amanda Jackson. A further search leads them to Amanda but despite Dean's best efforts he is unable to save her. Dean finds Joel and they find out that Joel was having an affair with his teacher and that was why Cassie ran away. They find a severely ...

2.title: Thrillseekers
2.plot: Dean rescues exotic dancer Jasmine from a high-rise but then gets caught in the middle of an extortion racket by her and one of her clients. Meanwhile, Lara risks her life to save Nick, an adrenaline junkie, from a flooded storm-water drain but she is then taunted by footage of the rescue through his website leading her to think about going on a potentially deadly base jump.

3.title: Fire in the Cross
3.plot: Jordan's best mate Willo is implicated as a suspect in the death of crime boss Sam Jenkins shortly after Dean and Lara rescue Sam from his firebombed nightclub. Things are not helped when Jordan sleeps with Willo's girlfriend Chelsea and Willo finds out. Elsewhere, a bet between Dean and the Fire Brigade's Jake Hudson over Lara exposes their naked rivalry in more ways that one. Meanwhile, Vince separates from his second wife.

4.title: Deathbed
4.plot: After a rock thrower causes a fatal collision Chase is left with a dilemma of whether to tell Tamsyn Taylor, the daughter of the woman who died, that the man she always thought was her father Colin is not her real dad and which leads to Tamsyn becoming obsessed with Chase. Elsewhere, Dean gives a DUI talk and finds Lara's fiancé Hamish is one of the attendees but Lara isn't aware of his drunk driving conviction. Meanwhile, Lara gets unwanted attention from a would-be Special Ops Rescue recruit and Dean is harassed by local heavy Gus, who wants money confiscated by ...

5.title: Ferry Disaster
5.plot: A drunk boat skipper crashes his cruiser into a chartered tourist ferry which in turn hits the wharf causing many casualties. Dean searches for the skipper who has mysteriously disappeared while Heidi tries to find out why a young girl on the wharf died suddenly after rescue arrived. Meanwhile, Dean and Chase meet their dad Shane's new and much younger girlfriend Fiona.

6.title: Building Site
6.plot: The team are called to a building site after a crane driver causes debris to fall after he crashes into the building. Michelle becomes overzealous on the site and finds that Ed Fraser's interference is not helping. But when she discovers that her lover Ian Johnson has feet of clay she ends up turning to Dean for comfort. Jordan becomes involved with the site's Health & Safety Coordinator Abigail and finds himself drawn into a web of sex, lies and sabotage. Meanwhile, Chase and Heidi's Rescue Truck is stolen and in order to get it back Vince makes a deal which involves...

7.title: Episode #1.7
7.plot: The team are called to a fairground where a ferris wheel has stuck with numerous people on board. Whilst investigating the problem Heidi and an engineer discover a victim of a serial rapist, who tasers his victims to subdue them. The victim is taken to hospital but later dies and Heidi is drawn to the victim's husband Karl Stevenson as she worries about his state of health. When the suspected rapist is chased by police and is injured Heidi cannot respond to help him. But have they apprehended the correct man? Elsewhere, Dean's ex-girlfriend Nicole comes back into his ...

8.title: Episode #1.8
8.plot: The team are called to an overturned vehicle but after rescuing the injured driver and passenger the team then discover a trapped man in the boot and discover the car was hi-jacked and the culprits were ATM robbers. Meanwhile, Dean and Chase's dad Shane is trapped in a collapsed trench and it takes help from Vince and Heidi to finally set him free. Elsewhere, Head Office send Chantelle Gregory to evaluate how the unit is working.

9.title: Rave
9.plot: Rescue are called to an illegal rave on the rocks at Gordons Bay and are met with casualties and a missing person. Chase befriends a young man named Brandon who is trapped in the rocks and ends up bonding with him when he decides to move out of home. But is Brandon all he seems? Elsewhere, Lara finds out about Hamish's DUI and his AA meetings and is in incensed with both him and Dean's cover-up.

10.title: Episode #1.10
10.plot: A gang of eco-terrorists blow up a sub-station in a busy shopping centre causing blackouts throughout the centre and the neighbouring areas. At the centre Rescue look for a young boy separated from his mother as they also deal with violent bodybuilder with rage issues. Meanwhile, Lara gets charmed by a burglar during the blackout and Nicole asks Dean to move in with her.

11.title: Episode #1.11
11.plot: Rescue Op are called to a vineyard where a bride is trapped in a runaway balloon. Meanwhile, Michelle receives a sexual harassment threat from head office and then finds her office has been bugged and her liaison with Dean on DVD. Elsewhere, a series of accidents on Rescue vehicles and equipment point to sabotage. Could they be linked to the DVD?

12.title: Episode #1.12
12.plot: Michelle gives Lara the job as Team Leader but it starts to go horribly wrong after a jealous wife sends rescue to find her husband in the Mount Kingston National Park on the pretense that he is lost and in need of insulin. After the team discover the husband perfectly safe they then have to deal with the wife exacting the real truth and causing an accident on a dam and endangering Lara after she is caught under the woman's car. But during the rescue Lara realises her feelings for Dean have turns to love just as she is about to marry Hamish. Meanwhile, Vince and ...

13.title: Episode #1.13
13.plot: Rescue are called to an emergency involving an oil tanker which crashed into several vehicles trying to avoid a pram. During the rescue they discover that the pram contained a crying doll and was created by the HQ intruder as he streamed the accident video to Lara's phone. After Lara leaves to return to Rescue HQ to prepare for her wedding Dean realises Lara's life is in danger from the violent stalker. But can he rescue her in time? Elsewhere, Heidi nominates Jordan as her fall-back guy if she hasn't met anyone by the time she is 30 and he agrees.

1.title: Enemy Mine
1.plot: The Team need to rescue a miner who gets trapped after an underground disaster.

2.title: A Day in the Death of Dean Gallagher
2.plot: A man on a jet-ski crashes into a marine fuel depot.

3.title: Locked In
3.plot: A woman is on the run from her ex-husband because of a custody fight of their two boys.

4.title: Jordan's Choice
4.plot: Jordan finds himself getting blackmailed after rescuing victims of crashed vehicle.

5.title: Shock Jock
5.plot: An explosion occurs at shock jock Zac Weston's party which Hamish is also attending. Meanwhile, Chase and Bingo clash over the correct procedures used at the explosion scene which leads Michelle to ponder transferring them both from the unit. But then Bingo takes it one step further by associating with a photographer from the explosion and ends up getting suspended indefinitely. Bingo manages to clear himself of his suspension but tragedy is not far away.

6.title: Thicker Than Water
6.plot: Following Bingo's death Dean sends Chase back to base after his reckless actions nearly sees him drown whilst trying to rescue a submerged female. Even though he maintains he is OK Michelle sends him to a psychiatrist and later after a heart-to-heart with his fiancée they break up. Meanwhile, back at the rescue site the team have to deal with the rescued female's boyfriend who is under attack from his brother over a crystal meth lab. Elsewhere, whilst choosing an engagement ring with Michelle Ian comes face to face with an assassin.

7.title: Find My Baby
7.plot: The team search for a missing girl after a car crashes into her house only to find that she died two years previously. When she checks out of a psych unit Dean becomes personally involved in trying to find her before she harms herself. Elsewhere, Michelle becomes over protective over her son James and Chase saves his counsellor from one of her patients.

8.title: Street Legal
8.plot: Vince tries unsuccessfully to draw his son Sam away from the world of drag racing as a vigilante patrols the streets intent in getting rid of drag racing in the area for good. Meanwhile, Chase and Emma's secret relationship hots up and Lara and Annika get along like a house on fire on a night out.

9.title: Out of the Ashes
9.plot: Michelle goes out of her way to cover up a sex scandal involving a female government minister which could compromise Rescue. Meanwhile, Dean finally realises his relationship with Annika has no future and breaks up with her.

10.title: Rock Stars
10.plot: Rescue attend a rock concert which has turned into a disaster area after a stage collapse. Meanwhile, Heidi's sister is rescued from the collapse but the reunion is anything but cordial.

11.title: Off the Rails
11.plot: A man, brainwashed by a cult, attempt to commit suicide on an underground railway line but ends up causing injury for passengers on the train. Whilst on the train Chase befriends a terrified witness who is running scared from a man intent on making sure she doesn't make it to testify.

12.title: One for the Money
12.plot: Rescue race to the bush to help the occupants of a light plane crash. However, a group of con-men are intent in getting to one of the men first where it turns out he embezzled money from a gang boss. Elsewhere, Michelle sees Vince's new girlfriend in a different light when she comes onto to Ian and Lara goes to see her estranged father at his nursing home.

13.title: Crazy Love
13.plot: Michelle's car is hijacked at traffic lights and the culprit drives off with James inside. A high-speed chase leads to the car crashing but with no sign of James in car. The car-jacker dies at the scene but not before he tells them he was paid to take James. Initially thinking it has something to do with Van Heusan's threats to Ian Vince and Rescue are shocked to discover that Ian's ex-girlfriend Renae and now Vince's girlfriend is the person behind it. A frantic search leads to a daring rescue of both James and Michelle. Elsewhere, Chase is injured during a rescue of...

locations: Bondi Beach, Sydney, New South Wales, Australia
Kings Cross, Sydney, New South Wales, Australia
St Leonards, Sydney, New South Wales, Australia
imdb.title: Rescue Special Ops
plot: Dean Gallagher and Chase are brothers. Competitive alpha males, they argue over everything, agree on nothing, but defend each other from outsiders no matter what. They're also members of the elite RESCUE Special Operations Unit.::Stephen Collins
